00:35:09,997 --> 00:35:13,018
Your hero should be driven by internal and external motivations.

756
00:35:14,539 --> 00:35:17,000
They should embark on a journey that forces them to change.

757
00:35:19,201 --> 00:35:21,362
And you should build a profile for your hero

758
00:35:21,742 --> 00:35:23,843
that is based on these themes and motivations.

759
00:35:24,243 --> 00:35:25,904
Something that you can always come back to and say,

760
00:35:25,924 --> 00:35:27,044
hey, would they do that?

761
00:35:27,665 --> 00:35:28,985
Does that make sense for this character?

762
00:35:31,010 --> 00:35:32,910
And design a supporting cast of characters

763
00:35:32,930 --> 00:35:35,651
that will complement or challenge your hero's goals.

764
00:35:36,492 --> 00:35:37,772
This is another important thing,

765
00:35:38,312 --> 00:35:40,713
and something that all of us are striving to get better at,

766
00:35:40,833 --> 00:35:44,895
is how can you make each supporting cast member

767
00:35:45,395 --> 00:35:48,156
as important and vital and well-rounded as your hero?

768
00:35:50,657 --> 00:35:52,217
And for the design, for the visual design,

769
00:35:52,797 --> 00:35:54,098
your hero should be iconic.

770
00:35:54,978 --> 00:35:55,979
Start with a silhouette.

771
00:35:56,499 --> 00:35:58,980
They should be recognizable without any internal detail.

772
00:35:59,883 --> 00:36:02,965
and design from the general, which is the broad silhouette,

773
00:36:03,305 --> 00:36:05,587
to the very specific, all the way down to that necklace.

774
00:36:06,087 --> 00:36:07,908
So you have to think about your characters,

775
00:36:07,928 --> 00:36:10,110
you're designing them through those different lenses.

776
00:36:11,891 --> 00:36:12,872
Try to cast an actor,

777
00:36:13,252 --> 00:36:14,673
even if you're not gonna work with an actor,

778
00:36:15,314 --> 00:36:18,896
imagine an actor that would give your character a soul,

779
00:36:19,817 --> 00:36:22,238
and then use that as inspiration

780
00:36:22,319 --> 00:36:24,200
for how they perform and how they work.

781
00:36:25,381 --> 00:36:27,522
And especially, in our case, how they would look.

782
00:36:30,477 --> 00:36:31,679
Wardrobe should be practical.

783
00:36:31,739 --> 00:36:32,581
This is my opinion.

784
00:36:32,661 --> 00:36:34,163
Some people don't believe in this.

785
00:36:34,303 --> 00:36:36,426
I just believe that the best heroes

786
00:36:36,527 --> 00:36:37,889
have the most practical garments.

787
00:36:38,390 --> 00:36:40,252
So think about clothes, not costumes.

788
00:36:41,156 --> 00:36:43,358
Think about even in the most stylized games,

789
00:36:43,538 --> 00:36:44,999
or like a character like Batman,

790
00:36:45,459 --> 00:36:48,641
every single thing on Batman's outfit serves a function.

791
00:36:49,282 --> 00:36:52,004
Even to the point of his silhouette, it invokes fear.

792
00:36:52,184 --> 00:36:54,806
So that is why he can look a little outrageous

793
00:36:54,906 --> 00:36:57,788
because he is trying to instill fear

794
00:36:57,908 --> 00:37:00,510
in an enemy that generally isn't afraid of anything.

795
00:37:02,011 --> 00:37:03,552
And every detail tells a story.

796
00:37:03,892 --> 00:37:05,594
Every single thing you do to your character

797
00:37:05,694 --> 00:37:06,234
is going to tell...

798
00:37:07,352 --> 00:37:09,554
the viewer what they should think about that character.

799
00:37:10,074 --> 00:37:12,696
So make sure you appoint your hero with props

800
00:37:13,397 --> 00:37:15,699
and reinforce those themes that you've talked about

801
00:37:15,819 --> 00:37:18,621
all the way at the profile into those details.

802
00:37:20,862 --> 00:37:21,883
And character execution.

803
00:37:23,324 --> 00:37:24,525
If you're making a realistic character,

804
00:37:24,845 --> 00:37:26,707
try to cast some models that match your design.

805
00:37:28,088 --> 00:37:30,069
Purchase or create clothes for your model

806
00:37:30,109 --> 00:37:31,310
to achieve maximum realism.

807
00:37:31,491 --> 00:37:32,731
Once again, if you're going for realism.

808
00:37:34,744 --> 00:37:38,809
Photogrammetry is an amazing process to be able to capture all this detail.

809
00:37:39,089 --> 00:37:42,934
And where we're living in games now are really embracing physically correct environments.

810
00:37:42,974 --> 00:37:47,640
You can get all the great detail off of those, from that photogrammetry information

811
00:37:47,941 --> 00:37:50,484
that will help make your character more physically correct.

812
00:37:52,382 --> 00:37:54,643
You want to capture the faces and clothes

813
00:37:55,063 --> 00:37:56,444
with extreme poses in mind.

814
00:37:56,804 --> 00:37:58,345
So not only what they look like in the base,

815
00:37:58,365 --> 00:37:59,685
but what do they look like in motion?

816
00:38:00,186 --> 00:38:02,747
And then hopefully your artists can infuse

817
00:38:02,787 --> 00:38:05,368
some of that detail into the character when they move.

818
00:38:07,539 --> 00:38:09,840
And prepare your asset with dynamic distress.

819
00:38:09,960 --> 00:38:12,301
Now once again, this is a style choice thing,

820
00:38:12,341 --> 00:38:14,342
but for every game I'll ever work on in the future,

821
00:38:14,362 --> 00:38:16,123
I'd love to see progression,

822
00:38:16,143 --> 00:38:18,564
and I'd love to see the character fit the world

823
00:38:18,604 --> 00:38:19,524
wherever they might be,

824
00:38:19,925 --> 00:38:23,786
whether they're covered in snow or ash or blood.

825
00:38:23,886 --> 00:38:25,567
Those things, if they're dynamic,

826
00:38:25,607 --> 00:38:26,848
they're that much more impactful.

827
00:38:28,892 --> 00:38:32,075
and connect the character to the world in action.

828
00:38:32,175 --> 00:38:34,557
So if you think about what your world is doing,

829
00:38:34,617 --> 00:38:36,419
your character should reflect those things

830
00:38:36,599 --> 00:38:38,721
on the model itself.

831
00:38:41,283 --> 00:38:42,784
And performance, the most important thing

832
00:38:43,685 --> 00:38:45,587
is bring your character life with a motion style

833
00:38:45,627 --> 00:38:46,928
that reinforces your theme.

834
00:38:48,680 --> 00:38:50,522
Performance capture is a great technology

835
00:38:51,122 --> 00:38:53,624
that you can capture even the most subtle performances

836
00:38:54,064 --> 00:38:57,587
from your actor and bring them and infuse them

837
00:38:57,627 --> 00:39:00,069
into your model with blend shapes and wrinkle maps.

838
00:39:00,089 --> 00:39:01,830
So this is getting a little bit more techie,

839
00:39:02,191 --> 00:39:03,952
but I absolutely love the new tech

840
00:39:03,972 --> 00:39:05,993
that we're able to embrace to bring subtlety

841
00:39:06,033 --> 00:39:06,734
to our characters.

842
00:39:08,215 --> 00:39:09,676
Think about contextual animations,

843
00:39:10,177 --> 00:39:12,919
things where your character and the world are related.

844
00:39:15,494 --> 00:39:17,435
One of the behaviors that we brought to Lara Croft

845
00:39:17,495 --> 00:39:19,798
is when she's cold, every time she goes near a fire,

846
00:39:19,818 --> 00:39:21,579
you'll see her rub her hands and warm her hands.

847
00:39:22,760 --> 00:39:25,062
You'll see when she's also cold

848
00:39:25,103 --> 00:39:27,204
and not near a source like that, she'll shiver.

849
00:39:28,005 --> 00:39:29,527
When she's in a tight, claustrophobic space,

850
00:39:29,547 --> 00:39:30,788
she'll put her hand up on the wall

851
00:39:31,188 --> 00:39:33,070
to recognize it and to crouch down.

852
00:39:33,691 --> 00:39:35,552
So really think about those contextual animations

853
00:39:35,592 --> 00:39:36,773
that make your character connect

854
00:39:37,154 --> 00:39:37,955
to the world that they're in.

855
00:39:39,474 --> 00:39:40,855
And think about secondary animation.

856
00:39:41,496 --> 00:39:42,537
You know, the primary animation,

857
00:39:42,577 --> 00:39:44,258
the primary locomotion is fantastic,

858
00:39:44,278 --> 00:39:46,140
but it's those secondary animations

859
00:39:46,580 --> 00:39:47,961
that really bring some life

860
00:39:48,262 --> 00:39:50,464
into what are essentially cycles.

861
00:39:51,885 --> 00:39:52,826
And if they're physics driven,

862
00:39:52,926 --> 00:39:55,588
you're going to see your cycles change

863
00:39:55,648 --> 00:39:57,310
based on whatever wind or conditions

864
00:39:57,330 --> 00:39:58,771
that you might have in the world.

865
00:40:01,030 --> 00:40:03,291
and reflect your character's growth through performance.

866
00:40:03,992 --> 00:40:05,173
As your story progresses,

867
00:40:05,914 --> 00:40:08,415
think about new behaviors or improvements to your character

868
00:40:08,736 --> 00:40:10,617
to continue to tell the story of their growth.

