00:41:08,620 --> 00:41:10,240
even if you're doing something abstract,

884
00:41:10,260 --> 00:41:12,161
like your character's a blob of goo,

885
00:41:14,281 --> 00:41:16,441
as long as you're thinking about their character

886
00:41:16,461 --> 00:41:18,662
and how they change and how they interact

887
00:41:18,682 --> 00:41:19,522
with the world that they're in,

888
00:41:19,882 --> 00:41:21,242
you can really do some amazing things.

889
00:41:21,282 --> 00:41:24,443
But it's really understanding some of those core principles

890
00:41:24,903 --> 00:41:27,924
that can help you at least construct a framework

891
00:41:28,264 --> 00:41:29,424
to build any new character.

892
00:41:29,784 --> 00:41:32,124
So all I'd recommend is,

893
00:41:34,312 --> 00:41:36,054
Don't think of these constructs as rules

894
00:41:36,075 --> 00:41:36,776
that you have to follow.

895
00:41:36,816 --> 00:41:38,118
Just think of them as information

896
00:41:38,138 --> 00:41:39,480
that you can always come back to

